# =============================================================================
# HRPlatform - Root Environment Variables Reference
# =============================================================================
#
# This is a REFERENCE file. Each app has its own .env / .env.local:
#
#   apps/api/.env          — Tenant API (NestJS, port 4000)
#   apps/admin-api/.env    — Admin API (NestJS, port 4001)
#   apps/web/.env.local    — Tenant Portal (Next.js, port 3000)
#   apps/admin/.env.local  — Admin Portal (Next.js, port 3001)
#   packages/database/.env — Prisma CLI (migrations, seeding)
#
# SETUP STEPS:
#   1. Copy each app's .env.example to .env (or .env.local for Next.js)
#   2. Generate secrets: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
#   3. Set DATABASE_URL to your PostgreSQL connection string
#   4. Ensure JWT_SECRET matches across: api, admin-api, web
#
# SECRET MANAGEMENT:
#   Development: .env files (gitignored)
#   Production:  Use your platform's secret manager:
#     - Vercel: Environment Variables in project settings
#     - AWS: Secrets Manager or SSM Parameter Store
#     - Docker: Docker secrets or env_file
#     - K8s: Kubernetes Secrets
#
# =============================================================================
#
# SHARED SECRETS (must match across apps):
#
#   JWT_SECRET        — apps/api + apps/admin-api + apps/web
#   DATABASE_URL      — apps/api + apps/admin-api + apps/web + packages/database
#
# APP-SPECIFIC SECRETS:
#
#   ENCRYPTION_KEY    — apps/api only (encrypts employee PII)
#   JWT_REFRESH_SECRET— apps/api only
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_*   — apps/api only (SSO)
#   SMTP_*            — apps/api only (email)
#
# =============================================================================
